<SLUG> BC-BBO-DIXIE-WORLD-SERIES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FLORIDA CHAMP GRABS BERTH IN DIXIE MAJORS FINAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEN HAYWARD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   EULESS, Texas _ In the first round of the Dixie Majors World
Series on Saturday, Hernando County, Fla., lost convincingly to
Georgia. Four days and four victories later, the Dixie Boys
Baseball state champion from Florida is in a good position to win
this year's title.
</P>
<P>
   Hernando County won its fourth consecutive game in the
tournament for 17-18-year-olds last night, defeating the previously
undefeated team from Monroe, La., 6-5, in 10 innings at The Parks
at Texas Star.
</P>
<P>
   Hernando County is one of three teams remaining with one loss,
along with Monroe and Lufkin. After the game, Hernando County won a
blind draw to earn a bye into today's title game.
</P>
<P>
   Monroe, La., is scheduled to face Lufkin in today's first game
at 4 p.m., and the winner will play Hernando County at 7 p.m. Both
Monroe and Lufkin will have to win two games to claim the title,
with Monroe forced to play in today's first game because it has
only played four games and the other two teams have played five in
the tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``Us 18-year-olds have been working for four years to get
here,'' said Chris Way, who was the starting pitcher for Hernando
County and scored the winning run. ``This game was intense from the
first inning. This is just awesome.''
</P>
<P>
   Hernando County won the game in the top of the 10th on a wild
pitch. Louisiana reliever Dustin Griggs walked Chris Cole and Way
to start the inning, then Stephen Blanton singled to right to load
the bases.
</P>
<P>
   Cole was thrown out at home by right fielder James Scalia when
Jason Dunn hit a bloop single to right. One pitch later, though,
the ball got away from Louisiana catcher Daniel Raymond and Way
scored.
</P>
<P>
   Florida reliever Nick Westbrook gave up two hits in the bottom
of the inning, but struck out Griggs to end the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``That is just a World Series,'' Florida coach Tim Sims said.
``I don't know what the Rangers and White Sox were doing \Rlast
night\S but we had some good baseball out here.''
</P>
<P>
   Through six innings it looked as if] Hernando County were going
to cruise into the tournament's final day after building a 5-1
lead. But in the bottom of the sixth, Hernando County had two
costly errors.
</P>
<P>
   Monroe scored two runs with the help of the miscues, then cut
the lead to 5-4 when Trey White scored on Stuart Tichenor's
sacrifice fly to center field.
</P>
<P>
   One inning later, Louisiana tied it at five when Philip Steele
misplayed a flyball, scoring Adam Hanks. Neither team scored in the
eighth or ninth, with Way pitching through the eighth and Louisiana
starter Matt Green going seven.
</P>
<P>
   ``We knew we would have to win two games to win coming into
\Rlast night\S,'' Louisiana coach Bruce Hanks said. ``And we've
still got to win two games.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
