<SLUG> BC-NESTLE-DIVISION-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NESTLE USA PARES POTATO_PROCESSING UNIT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS SIEROTY 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   GLENDALE, Calif. _ Nestle USA Inc. is selling its Food Services
Division's processed potato business to J.R. Simplot Co., a company
spokeswoman confirmed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but the purchased assets
have annual sales of more than $300 million. The deal is also
subject to regulatory approval and is expected to close within the
next 45 days.
</P>
<P>
   The three potato processing plants being sold are located in
Nampa and Othello, Idaho, and at Moses Lake, Wash.
</P>
<P>
   ``We viewed the Nestle business and the three plants as an
opportunity to expand our business,'' said J.R. Simplot spokesman
Fred Zerza. ``They have good plants, good people, and quality
customer service.''
</P>
<P>
   Rita Henderson, a Nestle spokeswoman, said after an extensive
evaluation of the potato business the company decided to
concentrate on other sectors.
</P>
<P>
   ``We determined that future opportunities for our long-term
profitable growth would be greater in other sectors of the food and
beverage categories in which we compete,'' said Henderson.
</P>
<P>
   Based in Boise, Idaho, J.R. Simplot has been in the potato
processing business for 60 years.
</P>
<P>
   Zerza said none of the 1,289 employees at the three plants is
expected to lose their jobs.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will honor the existing union contracts and it will be
business as usual at the three plants for the foreseeable future,''
he said.
</P>
<P>
   J.R. Simplot, a privately held agribusiness, has 12,000
employees and annual revenues of $2.7 billion. In addition to food
processing, the company is engaged in fertilizer manufacturing,
cattle feeding, farming and turf products.
</P>
<P>
   In the United States, Nestle's well-known brands include Nestle
Toll House, NesQuik, Carnation Coffee-mate and Friskies Fancy Feast
cat food. Nestle has 19,000 employees, $8 billion in sales and is
part of Swiss-based Nestle S.A., the world's largest food company.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
