<P>
   GOP-RDP-NYT (Philadelphia) _ A convention roundup: Republicans
open the final day of their national convention, preparing to make
Gov. George W. Bush of Texas their presidential nominee and
relishing the fight that he has already started with Vice President
Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: An early, 950-word version of the roundup has moved and
will be updated with a longer version from Philadelphia written by
R.W. Apple Jr., with quotes from late speeches; complete text of
Bush's speech will be available at the New York Times on the Web:
www.nytimes.com)
</P>
