   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-BUSH-SPEECH-NYT _ On the speech Gov. George W. Bush is
scheduled to deliver Thursday evening. The speech, which has been
ready for two months, and how it was prepared offer a window into
the discipline and strategy of the candidate and his campaign. By
Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   And sidebar: GOP-SPEECH-GERSON _ On the speechwriter, Mark
Gerson, an aide to Mayor Stephen Goldsmith of Indianapolis, Bush's
domestic affairs adviser.
