<P>
   GOP-ASSESS-NYT _ A news analysis on what the GOP has
accomplished and what lies ahead for them _ and for the Democrats.
By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-ECON-ASSESS-NYT _ The Bush campaign portrays his economic
agenda as all about helping single mothers and small business
owners. Just as Clinton worked to give Democrats a claim to fiscal
responsibility, Bush is working to give conservatism a claim to
solving social problems, but Bush is also seeking to avoid drawing
attention to the fact that his tax plan would largely benefit the
wealthy. And to the degree he engages Gore on economic issues, he
is moving onto tricky turf, given the widespread prosperity. By
Richard W. Stevenson. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-DONATIONS _ A look at some of the more subtle ways that some
corporations have found to donate money to the Republicans here
this week. By Don Van Natta Jr.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-CHENEY-NYT _ Speaking with the running mate. By Eric
Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-BUSH-FAMILY _ The day with the Bush family. By Nicholas D.
Kristof.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-FORD _ Doctors upgrade the condition of former President
Gerald Ford, a day after he was admitted to the neurological
intensive care unit of Hahnemann University Hospital in
Philadelphia after suffering at least one small stroke over the
last few days. ``The president should totally recover,'' said Dr.
Robert J. Schwartzman, the hospital's chief neurologist. By B.
Drummond Ayres Jr.
