<P>
   AIRPORT-POWER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS/FORT WORTH AIRPORT _ A power plant that creates
electricity from natural gas could be built at Dallas/Fort Worth
Airport in the next two years, a move that would give the airport
its own environmentally friendly power source. Airport officials
are considering building a combined-cycle cogeneration plant that
uses natural gas-powered turbines to make electricity, then uses
heat-capturing equipment to create steam for space heating. By
BRYON OKADA. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
