   EDs: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the current week. This
layout is available now.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0729: 2000 323i SPORT WAGON _ Although available
in other parts of the world for some time, it's only now that BMW's
compact 323i sport wagon, read station wagon, is available in the
United States. It can only enhance sales of the 3-Series line.
(DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 3-column
color photo of the 2000 323i sport wagon and a 2-column color photo
of the car's steering wheel.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 2000 323i sport wagon.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING _ One look at general sales trends of American
auto buyers will tell you that totally electric vehicles are facing
a steep uphill climb. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
Includes 1-column color photograph of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-FORD-SUV _ Russ reviews Ford's new SUV, the Escape
(DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 22. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ Tragic and senseless. Understandable,
but inexcusable. I am referring to two recent events: the tragic
death of a rookie Atlanta policeman who was mowed down by a driver
while in the act of doing his job and the teenage driver and
Transportation Department personnel who were hit by a driver using
the emergency lane as a passing lane. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ ATLANTA _ Last week, a student asked me what I
thought was the single most important pollution control device on
any passenger vehicle. Without hesitation, I mentioned the
catalytic converter. I elaborated on my statement with a little
history about the whys and wherefores that have brought the
internal combustion engine to its current ``almost
emission-friendly'' condition. (Carter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
