<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   WILLIAMS-400 _ WEST PALM BEACH, FLA. _ In an era when home-run
records have been shattered, many wonder whether Major League
Baseball will soon see the first .400 hitter in nearly 60 years.
Ted Williams, 81 and the last player to bat .400, says he
definitely thinks someone will. Williams also said he thinks that
someone is Nomar Garciaparra, the young shortstop for the Boston
Red Sox. (Capozzi, Palm Beach Post) MOVED Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTA-WILLIAMS _ Feature on former Texas Longhorn Christa
Williams, a pitcher for the USA women's national softball team. The
U.S. team played an exhibition doubleheader in College Station
Wednesday night. (Johnson, Austin American-Statesman). 15-18.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-MARYLAND-PREVIEW _ Road to College Football-Maryland.
Preview of the Terrapins, a rising program. (Arey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) 18.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-FREEAGENTS _ ATLANTA _ Doug Johnson and Maurice
Smith have something in common _ both are undrafted free agents
with the Falcons and have been impressive in the early going.
Similarities end there. Johnson comes from high profile Florida and
Smith is from NC A&AMP;T and didn't get much publicity in college. Both
are early surprises who may stick on Falcons roster. (Winkeljohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 22.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-INDY-POLE _ INDIANAPOLIS _ NASCAR qualifying for pole
position at Brickyard 400. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
13.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-EARNHARDTS _ ``The Son Also Rises `` a piece on Dale
Earnhardt Jr. who is blossoming this year and his dad, Dale Sr.,
who at 49 is having his best season in years. (Archdeacon, Dayton
Daily News) 35.
</P>
