</P>
<P>
   STREB. &QL; 
Elizabeth Streb will present her new high-impact multimedia
``Action Heroes,'' developed on the site in a three-week residency.
Performances on Aug. 11 and Aug. 12 at 7 p.m.; special event Friday
night at 6; open rehearsals Friday, Saturday and Aug. 8-12 at 2
p.m. Free. Vanderbilt Hall, Grand Central Terminal; (212) 340-2210
or &QL; 
www.grandcentralterminal.com.
</P>
<P>
   URBAN BUSH WOMEN. &QL; 
Jawole Willa Jo Zollar and the Urban Bush Women in two dances that
celebrate everything from a woman's bottom to her psyche. Aug. 18
at 7 p.m.; food is served from 6 to 7 p.m. Free. La Plaza Cultural
community garden, Avenue C at Ninth Street, East Village; (212)
674-8194.
</P>
<P>
   FOLK PARKS 2000. &QL; 
A day of performances and participatory dance from eight nations.
Sept. 9, beginning at noon. Free. Damrosch Park Band Shell, Lincoln
Center; (212) 571-1555 or www.ctmd.org.
</P>
