</P>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA _ So, we are all here at the Republican National
Convention in Philadelphia. Delegates from across America in
boaters and baseball caps, stetsons and straw hats, some with blue
rinses and some with body piercings, have travelled here. Their
diverse backgrounds are irrelevant, we're told; what is important,
it is made clear roughly every ten minutes or so, is that we are
here ``together.''...By Andrew Marshall, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary, Political Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (600 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE `DEMOCRATIC FAMILY' _ WHERE KIDS MAKE BIG DECISIONS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; KIDS-ARE-BOSS-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ The days when father's word was law have
disappeared, with children as young as eight now having a big say
in many British households. Research published Monday shows the
Victorian approach to child-rearing, where children were seen but
not heard, has collapsed over the past 30 years with the birth of
the new ``democratic family.''...By Cherry Norton, The Independent &QL;
</P>
