<P>
   CVN-CONVENTION-RDP (Philadelphia) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush
accepts his party's presidential nomination in a speech in which he
is expected to talk about the Clinton years in a ``regretful tone,
not a harsh tone,'' according to his press secretary. He is also
expected to tell the delegates that this is a ``unique moment'' of
peace and prosperity that provides the opportunity to solve some
long-standing problems. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   CVN-MAIN (Philadelphia) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush claims the
Republican presidential nomination Thursday night promising to do
things ``differently'' than Bill Clinton and Al Gore. By ALAN
