<SLUG> BC-FORD-CONDITION-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FORD LISTED IN FAIR CONDITION 
 
 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By LETITIA STEIN 
c.200 Houston Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA _ Former President Ford exercised and visited with
family members at a hospital here Thursday as doctors monitored his
recovery from a stroke suffered while attending the Republican
National Convention.
</P>
<P>
   The 87-year-old Republican was upgraded from ``serious'' to
``fair'' condition but remained in the intensive care unit at
Hahnemann University Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Among Ford's visitors were Republican presidential nominee Gov.
George W. Bush, who said the former president was ``doing great.''
</P>
<P>
   ``He told me to tell people that he can't wait to get out and
campaign with me in a couple of weeks,'' Bush said.
</P>
<P>
   Doctors also reported that Ford was in ``good spirits,'' with
his health noticeably improved.
</P>
<P>
   Ford was hospitalized Wednesday morning after experiencing
unsteady balance and difficulty speaking. Doctors diagnosed a brain
stem stroke and admitted him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very pleased to report the president's doing much
better,'' said Robert Schwartzman, the hospital's chief of
neurology. ``He's walking, his balance is better, his left hand has
returned to normal.''
</P>
<P>
   Doctors learned in conversations with former first lady Betty
Ford that her husband exhibited symptoms this week that suggest he
suffered an earlier stroke. However, doctors have clinical evidence
of only one stroke.
</P>
<P>
   A family spokesperson said doctors encouraged Ford to receive a
CAT scan when he sought treatment for facial pain Tuesday night
after he and other former GOP presidents were honored at the
Republican convention. Ford decided at the time not to undergo
further evaluation.
</P>
<P>
   The former president has been placed on blood-thinning
medication but will not require rehabilitation at home. Doctors
anticipate ``100 percent'' recovery.
</P>
<P>
   Ford chatted with his wife and family members Thursday. He could
be released as early as this weekend. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXEND OF STORY &QL; 
$$$
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
